The paper deals with the decomposition of graphs into cliques and circular-arc graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The algorithms presented in the paper have time complexity as a key aspect, which is a common focus in computational geometry (cs.CG) and theoretical computer science (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the tree-width of graphs, which is a topic in both graph theory and machine learning (cs.LG).
